  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Louis Dreyfus COVID-19 Climate-Resilient Smallholder Farmer Recovery Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Senior unsecured 3-year USD bullet loan of $100 million to finance LDC&apos;s working capital needs in Asia for the sustainable procurement of coffee, cotton, and rice. The transaction will preserve the livelihood and climate resilience of [60,000] smallholder farmers affected by COVID-19 in the five project countries. A complementing TA (funded by trust funds) will establish 80 farmer groups and train 160 farmer group educators with an aim to help farmers obtain sustainability certifications.</narrative>
  </description>
